<paragraph blockId="7.[151,567,547,574]" box="[151,567,547,574]" pageId="7" pageNumber="585">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,567,547,574]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="7" pageNumber="585" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,567,547,574]" pageId="7" pageNumber="585">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Brauer 1870" authorityName="Brauer" authorityYear="1870" box="[238,567,547,574]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Xiphocentron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="585" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,404,547,574]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="585">Xiphocentron</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Brauer, F. M." box="[412,567,547,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="585" pagination="66" refId="ref5107" refString="Brauer, F. M. (1870) Uber Xiphocentron, eine neue Hydropsychidengattung. Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 20, 66." type="journal article" year="1870">Brauer 1870</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="585" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,619,718]" pageId="7" pageNumber="585">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brauer" authorityYear="1870" box="[280,431,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Xiphocentron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="585" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[280,431,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="585">Xiphocentron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is represented in the Neotropics by about 53 species distributed among five subgenera (
<bibRefCitation author="Schmid, F." box="[159,317,655,681]" pageId="7" pageNumber="585" pagination="1 - 126" refId="ref6761" refString="Schmid, F. (1982) La famille des Xiphocentronides (Trichoptera: Annulipalpia). Memoires de la Societe Entomologique du Canada, 121, 1 - 126. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / entm 114122 fv" type="journal article" year="1982">Schmid 1982</bibRefCitation>
). Four species in three subgenera were previously known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1062,1154,656,682]" name="Panama" pageId="7" pageNumber="585">Panama</collectingCountry>
. Here we add one more species in a fourth subgenus, 
<emphasis box="[481,648,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="585">Glyphocentron</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
